measurements.name: Gamma-Ray Intensity
measurements.description: The intensity of natural gamma-ray radiation emitted from formations containing radioactive elements, such as Potassium, Thorium, and Uranium. Measured according to API specifications.

measurements.name: Gamma Ray Minus Uranium
measurements.description: The measurement of the naturally occurring gamma radiation less the radiation attributed to uranium.

measurements.name: Induced Gamma-Ray Intensity
measurements.description: Intensity of gamma-ray radiation which has been induced, either chemically or by nuclear activation.

measurements.name: Spatial Gamma Radiation Intensity
measurements.description: Intensity of gamma radiation represented as a function of a spatial path.

measurements.name: Spectral Gamma Radiation Intensity
measurements.description: Intensity of gamma radiation represented as a function of wavelength.

measurements.name: Potassium Concentration As API Gamma Ray
Quality Indicator As API Gamma Ray
Response Parameter As API Gamma Ray
Standard Deviation As API Gamma Ray
Thorium Concentration As API Gamma Ray
Uranium Concentration As API Gamma Ray
API Neutron
measurements.description: The Neutron calibration measurement determined using the API test pit. This quantity is associated with the natural formation hydrogen concentration.

measurements.name: API Gravity
measurements.description: A measure of hydrocarbon density equal to 141.5/(specific gravity @ 60 degF) - 131.5; usually reported with a temperature.

measurements.name: Fluid Density As API Oil Gravity
Oil Density As API Oil Gravity
Acceleration
measurements.description: The rate of variation of velocity with time.

measurements.name: Gravitational Field Strength
measurements.description: Strength of the gravitational field at some location. Also referred to as the acceleration of gravity, measured in units of acceleration.

measurements.name: X Gravity
measurements.description: Strength of the x-axis component of the gravitational field at some location.

measurements.name: Y Gravity
measurements.description: Strength of the y-axis component of the gravitational field at some location.

measurements.name: Z Gravity
measurements.description: Strength of the z-axis component of the gravitational field at some location; used to correct total z-axis acceleration of a logging tool to compute actual tool movement.

measurements.name: Velocity Gradient In Time
measurements.description: First derivative of velocity versus time.

measurements.name: Velocity K Factor In Time
measurements.description: Velocity time gradient, dv/dt used in some velocity functions like linear velocity : v(t) = v_0 + k*t : v(t,t_1) = v_0 + k_1*t_1 + k_2*(t-t_1)

measurements.name: Amount Of Substance
measurements.description: The amount of a particular substance (e.g. chemical) expressed in units of moles.

measurements.name: Equivalent Amount
measurements.description: The amount of substance which react with or supply one mole of hydrogen ions (or electrons)

measurements.name: Area
measurements.description: The two-dimensional extent of some region of interest.

measurements.name: Permeability
measurements.description: A property of rock (formation) denoting its ability to pass fluids through its interconnected pores. Permeability is estimated from measurements on well tests, cores, production results or logs.

measurements.name: Absolute Permeability
measurements.description: The permeability of porous material when completely saturated with a wetting fluid and without the influence of non-Darcy (turbulence) effects. Also called "intrinsic" permeability.

measurements.name: Absolute Permeability - Gas
measurements.description: The permeability of porous material when completely saturated with gas.
